<h3 class="step-title">Step 2 - Design Options</h3>
<p class="step-description">Please select the options that will be applied during the design of the ribozyme.</p>
<div class="step-contents design-content">
  <div id="designAlert" class="alert alert-error invisible"></div>
  <form id="design-form" accept-charset="utf-8">
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="region">
	<legend class="section-collapse" speed="200">    Regions for Target Design
	  <i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i>
	</legend>
	<div class="offset2">
	  <input type="checkbox" name="region" value="5'"/> 5'UTR<br/>
	  <input type="checkbox" name="region" value="ORF" checked="checked"/> Open Reading Frame (ORF)<br/>
	  <input type="checkbox" name="region" value="3'"/> 3'UTR<br/>
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="region-help">
	Select what part of the RNA you will be targeting. No cut-sites (NUH) outside the selected areas will be considered.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="env">
	<legend class="section-collapse" speed="200">    Target Environment
	  <i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i>
	</legend>
	<div class="offset2">
	  <input type="radio" required="true" name="env" value="vitro"/> In-vitro<br/>
	  <input type="radio" required="true" name="env" value="vivo"/> In-vivo<br/>
	  <select name="envVivo" id="envVivo">
            <option value="mouse (taxid:10090)" selected="selected">Mouse</option>
            <option value="rat (taxid:10114)">Rat</option>
            <option value="human (taxid:9606)">Human</option>
            <option value="Daphnia (taxid:6668)">Daphnia</option>
	    <option value="other">Other</option>
	  </select><br/>
	  <label for="otherEnv" class="otherEnv invisible">    Find your organism <a href="http://blast.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/Blast.cgi?PROGRAM=blastn&BLAST_PROGRAMS=megaBlast&PAGE_TYPE=BlastSearch" target="_blank">here</a></label>
	  <input id="otherEnv" class="invisible otherEnv" type="text" name="otherEnv" placeholder="Example: mouse (taxid:10090)" />
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="target-help">
	Select what environment the ribozyme will be tested on.
	If in-vivo, you may specify an organism so that we may
	test that the ribozyme does not anneal to off-target locations.
  If the organism is not in the list, you may select other. You will then be prompted for a tax-id that can be found in the 'Blast' site. In the organism text box, you can find all organisms that NCBI has in their data base, then copy the tax-id unto this website.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="envProperties">
	<legend class="section-collapse" speed="200">    Environment Properties
	  <i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i></legend>
	<div class="offset2">
	  <label for="temperature">Temperature</label>
	  <input type="number" min="0" name="temperature" value="37"/> &#176;C<br/>
	  <label for="naC">Na&#8314; Concentration</label>
	  <input type="number" min="0" name="naC" value="150"/> mM<br/>
	  <label for="mgC">Mg<sup>2</sup>&#8314; Concentration</label>
	  <input type="number" min="0" name="mgC" value="0"/> mM<br/>
	  <label for="oligoC">Oligomer Concentration</label>
	  <input type="number" min="0" name="oligoC" value="200"/> nM<br/>
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="env-help">
	Provide details of the environment in which the ribozyme will 
	be used. This will allow for optimization over a wide range of
        annealing temperatures, and will help the algorithm
	predict better the secondary structure of the ribozyme.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="cutsites">
	<legend class="section-collapse" speed="200">    Potential Cut-sites
	  <i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i></legend>
	<div class="offset2">
	  <label for="cutsites">Preferred cut-site(s)</label>
	  <select name="cutsites" multiple="multiple">
	    <option selected="selected" value="GUC">GUC</option>
	    <option value="CUC">CUC</option>
	    <option value="AUC">AUC</option>
	    <option value="UUC">UUC</option>
	    <option value="AUA">AUA</option>
	    <option value="UUC">UUA</option>
	    <option value="GUA">GUA</option>
	    <option value="CUA">CUA</option>
	    <option value="GUU">GUU</option>
	    <option value="CUU">CUU</option>
	    <option value="AUU">AUU</option>
	    <option value="UUU">UUU</option>
	  </select>
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="cutsites-help">
	Select one or multiple cut-sites for attachment on the target. Please note that a larger number of cut-sites means increased work-load and thus more waiting time. It is recommended that you use GUC and another alternate cut-site, but not more.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="shape">
	<legend class="section-collapse" speed="200">    Ribozyme Shape<i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i></legend>
	<div class="offset2">  
          <input type="radio" name="foldShape" value="Basic" checked="checked"> Minimal (before 2003)</input><br/>
          <input type="radio" name="foldShape" value="Wishbone"> Wishbone (discovered in 2003)</input>
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="shape-help">
	Choose the catalytic core that will be used to design the ribozyme.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="advanced-arm">
	<legend class="section-expand" speed="200" >    Advanced Options - Arms Length<i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i></legend>
	<div class="offset2" id="arm-options">
	  <label for="left_arm_min">Helix I Minimum Length</label>
	  <input type="number" name="left_arm_min" value="5"/> nucleotides<br/>
	  <label for="left_arm_max">Helix I Maximum Length</label>
	  <input type="number" name="left_arm_max" value="10"/> nucleotides<br/>
	  <label for="right_arm_min">Helix III Minimum Length</label>
	  <input type="number" name="right_arm_min" value="5"/> nucleotides<br/>
	  <label for="right_arm_max">Helix III Maximum Length</label>
	  <input type="number" name="right_arm_max" value="10"/> nucleotides<br/>
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="arm-help">
	These parameters relate to the length of the various helices on the ribozyme.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="advanced-promoter">
	<legend class="section-expand" speed="200" >    Advanced Options - T7 Promoter<i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i></legend>
	<div class="offset2">
	  <label for="promoter">Append T7 Promoter?</label>
	  <input type="radio" name="promoter" value="1"/> Yes<br/>
	  <input type="radio" name="promoter" value="0" checked="checked"/> No<br/>
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="promoter-help">
          If the checkbox is checked, the T7 promoter will be added to the final DNA. If desired this should be used in vitro.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="design-form-cat">
      <fieldset class="option-field" name="advanced-specificity">
	<legend class="section-expand" speed="200" >    Advanced Options - Specificity<i class="icon-question-sign pull-right"></i></legend>
	<div class="offset2">
	  <input type="radio" name="specificity" value="cleavage" checked="checked"/> Cleavage Only<br/>
	  <input type="radio" name="specificity" value="hybrid"/> Cleavage and Hybridization<br/>
	</div>
      </fieldset>
      <div class="well well-lg well-help invisible" id="specificity-help">
          When verifying specificity, we can either find off-target locations where the ribozyme will cleave or it will
          hybridize strongly enough to silence the gene. If you select cleavage-only, non-cleaving sites will not be considered.
      </div>
    </div>
  </form>
  <div id="designAlert2" class="alert alert-error invisible"></div>
  <div class="step-buttons">
    <button id="backStep1" class="btn btn-large">Back</button>
    <a href="#step3" id="submit2" class="submit btn btn-primary btn-large">Submit</a>
  </div>
</div>
